FBIS4-63808 "drsov101_a_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-101 Daily Report 24 May 1994 RUSSIAN INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Russia Wants Ukraine Navy Moved From Sevastopol Russia Wants Ukraine Navy Moved From Sevastopol LD2405164194 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1551 GMT 24 May 94 LD2405164194 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Russian BFN [Text] Russia is proposing to make Sevastopol the main base for the Russian part of the Black Sea Fleet and to relocate the Ukrainian navy outside of the town. Options include having the Ukraine navy stationed in Balaklava, in Crimea, or in Odessa. Our correspondent was told this by unofficial sources. Those unofficial sources think that a final document may be signed this evening.
